This is either erroneous or just plain silly. There is no security
classification called "Classified".

>
>And then there's the note scribbled by J. Edgar Hoover when he found out that
>Jean Paul Sartres was a Communist:  "Find out who Sartres is!"

It's "Sartre". That suggests you need to be a bit more careful in repeating
anecdotes, as there's some evidence that at a minimum they get garbled
somewhere before we hear them from you.

